  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Rousanara Begum versus S.K. Salahuddin @ SK Salauddin & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_12_273_280','2025INSC1375'); ><font size='4'> <strong>ROUSANARA BEGUM<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>S.K. SALAHUDDIN @ SK SALAUDDIN & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 12 S.C.R. 273</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1375</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006672025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KAROL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, N KOTISWAR SINGH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether goods given to a daughter at the time of her marriage by her father, or to the bridegroom, can be by application of law, returned to the daughter-appellant given that their marriage had ended in divorce. Headnotes&dagger; Muslim on Divorce) Act, 1986 &ndash; s.3 &ndash; Mahr or other properties of Muslim woman to be given to her at the time of divorce &ndash; Goods given to a daughter at the time of her marriage by her father, or to the bridegroom, if by application of law, can be returned to the daughter-appellant<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 02-12-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 5164/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_12_273_280','2025INSC1375','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col